       <h2>Try It At Home: A Beginner EMOM Workout</h2> 
         <p>    Want to see what it's all about? You don't need a fully equipped Box to try CrossFit. Here is a simple 12-Minute EMOM you can do right in your living room.</p>
       <h3>How it works:</h3> <p> Set a timer for 12 minutes. At the beginning of each minute, perform the listed exercise. Once you finish the reps, use the remaining time in that minute to rest. When the next minute starts, move to the next exercise. Repeat the entire 3-minute cycle 4 times!  </p>
        <ul>    
        <li>  <h4>Minute 1:</h4> <p> Air Squats  </p> </li>
       <hr />   
    <li> <h4> Minute 2: </h4> <p> 10 Push-ups (modify by dropping to your knees if needed) </p>   </li>
         <hr /> 
    <li> <h4>  Minute 3: </h4>  <p> 15 Sit-ups </p> </li>
</ul>
      <p> if the workout is too easy feel free to try harder veriations of these exersizes</p>
       
